1440  MSGARK_RTFUNC_FAILED, ark_mem->ark_tlo);
1441  return(ARK_RTFUNC_FAIL);
1442  } else if (retval == RTFOUND) {
1443  ark_mem->ark_tretlast = *tret = ark_mem->ark_tlo;
1444  return(ARK_ROOT_RETURN);
1445  }
1446 
1447  /* If tn is distinct from tretlast (within roundoff),
1448  check remaining interval for roots */
1449  if ( SUNRabs(ark_mem->ark_tn - ark_mem->ark_tretlast) > troundoff ) {
1450 
1451  retval = arkRootCheck3(ark_mem);
1452 
1453  if (retval == ARK_SUCCESS) { /* no root found */
1454  ark_mem->ark_irfnd = 0;
1455  if ((irfndp == 1) && (itask == ARK_ONE_STEP)) {
1456  ark_mem->ark_tretlast = *tret = ark_mem->ark_tn;
1457  N_VScale(ONE, ark_mem->ark_ycur, yout);
1458  return(ARK_SUCCESS);
1459  }
1460  } else if (retval == RTFOUND) { /* a new root was found */
1461  ark_mem->ark_irfnd = 1;
1462  ark_mem->ark_tretlast = *tret = ark_mem->ark_tlo;
1463  return(ARK_ROOT_RETURN);
1464  } else if (retval == ARK_RTFUNC_FAIL) { /* g failed */
1465  arkProcessError(ark_mem, ARK_RTFUNC_FAIL, "ARKODE", "arkRootCheck3",
1466  MSGARK_RTFUNC_FAILED, ark_mem->ark_tlo);
1467  return(ARK_RTFUNC_FAIL);
1468  }
1469 
1470  }
1471 
1472  } /* end of root stop check */
1473 
1474  /* In ARK_NORMAL mode, test if tout was reached */
1475  if ( (itask == ARK_NORMAL) &&
1476  ((ark_mem->ark_tn-tout)*ark_mem->ark_h >= ZERO) ) {
1477  ark_mem->ark_tretlast = *tret = tout;
1478  ier = ARKodeGetDky(ark_mem, tout, 0, yout);
1479  if (ier != ARK_SUCCESS) {
1480  arkProcessError(ark_mem, ARK_ILL_INPUT, "ARKODE",
1481  "ARKode", MSGARK_BAD_TOUT, tout);
1482  return(ARK_ILL_INPUT);
1483  }
1484  return(ARK_SUCCESS);
1485  }
1486 
1487  /* In ARK_ONE_STEP mode, test if tn was returned */
1488  if ( itask == ARK_ONE_STEP &&
1489  SUNRabs(ark_mem->ark_tn - ark_mem->ark_tretlast) > troundoff ) {
1490  ark_mem->ark_tretlast = *tret = ark_mem->ark_tn;
1491  N_VScale(ONE, ark_mem->ark_ycur, yout);
1492  return(ARK_SUCCESS);
1493  }
1494 
1495  /* Test for tn at tstop or near tstop */
1496  if ( ark_mem->ark_tstopset ) {
1497 
1498  if ( SUNRabs(ark_mem->ark_tn - ark_mem->ark_tstop) <= troundoff) {
1499  ier = ARKodeGetDky(ark_mem, ark_mem->ark_tstop, 0, yout);
1500  if (ier != ARK_SUCCESS) {
1501  arkProcessError(ark_mem, ARK_ILL_INPUT, "ARKODE", "ARKode",
1502  MSGARK_BAD_TSTOP, ark_mem->ark_tstop, ark_mem->ark_tn);
1503  return(ARK_ILL_INPUT);
1504  }
1505  ark_mem->ark_tretlast = *tret = ark_mem->ark_tstop;
1506  ark_mem->ark_tstopset = FALSE;
1507  return(ARK_TSTOP_RETURN);
1508  }
1509 
1510  /* If next step would overtake tstop, adjust stepsize */
1511  if ( (ark_mem->ark_tn + ark_mem->ark_hprime - ark_mem->ark_tstop)*ark_mem->ark_h > ZERO ) {
1512  ark_mem->ark_hprime = (ark_mem->ark_tstop - ark_mem->ark_tn)*(ONE-FOUR*ark_mem->ark_uround);
1513  ark_mem->ark_eta = ark_mem->ark_hprime/ark_mem->ark_h;
1514  }
1515  }
1516  } /* end stopping tests block */
1517 
1518 
1519  /*--------------------------------------------------
1520  4. Looping point for internal steps
1521 
1522  - update the ewt vector for the next step
1523  - check for errors (too many steps, too much
1524  accuracy requested, step size too small)
1525  - take a new step (via arkStep); stop on error
1526  - perform stop tests:
1527  - check for root in last step taken
1528  - check if tout was passed
1529  - check if close to tstop
1530  - check if in ONE_STEP mode (must return)
1531  --------------------------------------------------*/
1532  nstloc = 0;
1533  for(;;) {
1534 
1535  ark_mem->ark_next_h = ark_mem->ark_h;
1536 
1537  /* Reset and check ewt */
1538  if (ark_mem->ark_nst > 0 && !ark_mem->ark_resized) {
1539  ewtsetOK = ark_mem->ark_efun(ark_mem->ark_ycur,
1540  ark_mem->ark_ewt,
1541  ark_mem->ark_e_data);
1542  if (ewtsetOK != 0) {
1543  if (ark_mem->ark_itol == ARK_WF)
1544  arkProcessError(ark_mem, ARK_ILL_INPUT, "ARKODE", "ARKode",
1545  MSGARK_EWT_NOW_FAIL, ark_mem->ark_tn);
1546  else
1547  arkProcessError(ark_mem, ARK_ILL_INPUT, "ARKODE", "ARKode",
1548  MSGARK_EWT_NOW_BAD, ark_mem->ark_tn);
1549 
1550  istate = ARK_ILL_INPUT;
1551  ark_mem->ark_tretlast = *tret = ark_mem->ark_tn;
1552  N_VScale(ONE, ark_mem->ark_ycur, yout);
1553  break;
1554  }
1555  }
1556 
1557  /* Reset and check rwt */
1558  if (!ark_mem->ark_rwt_is_ewt) {
1559  if (ark_mem->ark_nst > 0 && !ark_mem->ark_resized) {
1560  ewtsetOK = ark_mem->ark_rfun(ark_mem->ark_ycur,
1561  ark_mem->ark_rwt,
1562  ark_mem->ark_r_data);
1563  if (ewtsetOK != 0) {
1564  if (ark_mem->ark_itol == ARK_WF)
1565  arkProcessError(ark_mem, ARK_ILL_INPUT, "ARKODE", "ARKode",
1566  MSGARK_RWT_NOW_FAIL, ark_mem->ark_tn);
1567  else
1568  arkProcessError(ark_mem, ARK_ILL_INPUT, "ARKODE", "ARKode",
1569  MSGARK_RWT_NOW_BAD, ark_mem->ark_tn);
1570 
1571  istate = ARK_ILL_INPUT;
1572  ark_mem->ark_tretlast = *tret = ark_mem->ark_tn;
1573  N_VScale(ONE, ark_mem->ark_ycur, yout);
1574  break;
1575  }
1576  }
1577  }
1578 
1579  /* Check for too many steps */
1580  if ( (ark_mem->ark_mxstep>0) && (nstloc >= ark_mem->ark_mxstep) ) {
1581  arkProcessError(ark_mem, ARK_TOO_MUCH_WORK, "ARKODE", "ARKode",
1582  MSGARK_MAX_STEPS, ark_mem->ark_tn);
1583  istate = ARK_TOO_MUCH_WORK;
1584  ark_mem->ark_tretlast = *tret = ark_mem->ark_tn;
1585  N_VScale(ONE, ark_mem->ark_ycur, yout);
1586  break;
1587  }
1588 
1589  /* Check for too much accuracy requested */
1590  nrm = N_VWrmsNorm(ark_mem->ark_ycur, ark_mem->ark_ewt);
1591  ark_mem->ark_tolsf = ark_mem->ark_uround * nrm;
1592  if (ark_mem->ark_tolsf > ONE) {
1593  arkProcessError(ark_mem, ARK_TOO_MUCH_ACC, "ARKODE", "ARKode",
1594  MSGARK_TOO_MUCH_ACC, ark_mem->ark_tn);
1595  istate = ARK_TOO_MUCH_ACC;
1596  ark_mem->ark_tretlast = *tret = ark_mem->ark_tn;
1597  N_VScale(ONE, ark_mem->ark_ycur, yout);
1598  ark_mem->ark_tolsf *= TWO;
1599  break;
1600  } else {
1601  ark_mem->ark_tolsf = ONE;
1602  }
1603 
1604  /* Check for h below roundoff level in tn */
1605  if (ark_mem->ark_tn + ark_mem->ark_h == ark_mem->ark_tn) {
1606  ark_mem->ark_nhnil++;
1607  if (ark_mem->ark_nhnil <= ark_mem->ark_mxhnil)
1608  arkProcessError(ark_mem, ARK_WARNING, "ARKODE", "ARKode",
1609  MSGARK_HNIL, ark_mem->ark_tn, ark_mem->ark_h);
1610  if (ark_mem->ark_nhnil == ark_mem->ark_mxhnil)
1611  arkProcessError(ark_mem, ARK_WARNING, "ARKODE", "ARKode",
1612  MSGARK_HNIL_DONE);
1613  }
1614 
1615  /* Call arkStep to take a step */
1616  kflag = arkStep(ark_mem);
1617 
1618  /* Process failed step cases, and exit loop */
1619  if (kflag != ARK_SUCCESS) {
1620  istate = arkHandleFailure(ark_mem, kflag);
1621  ark_mem->ark_tretlast = *tret = ark_mem->ark_tn;
1622  N_VScale(ONE, ark_mem->ark_ycur, yout);
1623  break;
1624  }
1625 
1626  nstloc++;
1627 
1628  /* Check for root in last step taken. */
1629  if (ark_mem->ark_nrtfn > 0) {
1630 
1631  retval = arkRootCheck3(ark_mem);
1632  if (retval == RTFOUND) { /* A new root was found */
1633  ark_mem->ark_irfnd = 1;
1634  istate = ARK_ROOT_RETURN;
1635  ark_mem->ark_tretlast = *tret = ark_mem->ark_tlo;
1636  break;
1637  } else if (retval == ARK_RTFUNC_FAIL) { /* g failed */
1638  arkProcessError(ark_mem, ARK_RTFUNC_FAIL, "ARKODE", "arkRootCheck3",
1639  MSGARK_RTFUNC_FAILED, ark_mem->ark_tlo);
1640  istate = ARK_RTFUNC_FAIL;
1641  break;
1642  }
1643 
1644  /* If we are at the end of the first step and we still have
1645  * some event functions that are inactive, issue a warning
1646  * as this may indicate a user error in the implementation
1647  * of the root function. */
1648  if (ark_mem->ark_nst==1) {
1649  inactive_roots = FALSE;
1650  for (ir=0; ir<ark_mem->ark_nrtfn; ir++) {
1651  if (!ark_mem->ark_gactive[ir]) {
1652  inactive_roots = TRUE;
1653  break;
1654  }
1655  }
1656  if ((ark_mem->ark_mxgnull > 0) && inactive_roots) {
1657  arkProcessError(ark_mem, ARK_WARNING, "ARKODES", "ARKode",
1658  MSGARK_INACTIVE_ROOTS);
1659  }
1660  }
1661  }
1662 
1663  /* In NORMAL mode, check if tout reached */
1664  if ( (itask == ARK_NORMAL) &&
1665  (ark_mem->ark_tn-tout)*ark_mem->ark_h >= ZERO ) {
1666  istate = ARK_SUCCESS;
1667  ark_mem->ark_tretlast = *tret = tout;
1668  (void) ARKodeGetDky(ark_mem, tout, 0, yout);
1669  ark_mem->ark_next_h = ark_mem->ark_hprime;
1670  break;
1671  }
1672 
1673  /* Check if tn is at tstop or near tstop */
1674  if ( ark_mem->ark_tstopset ) {
1675  troundoff = FUZZ_FACTOR*ark_mem->ark_uround *
1676  (SUNRabs(ark_mem->ark_tn) + SUNRabs(ark_mem->ark_h));
1677  if ( SUNRabs(ark_mem->ark_tn - ark_mem->ark_tstop) <= troundoff) {
1678  (void) ARKodeGetDky(ark_mem, ark_mem->ark_tstop, 0, yout);
1679  ark_mem->ark_tretlast = *tret = ark_mem->ark_tstop;
1680  ark_mem->ark_tstopset = FALSE;
1681  istate = ARK_TSTOP_RETURN;
1682  break;
1683  }
1684  if ( (ark_mem->ark_tn + ark_mem->ark_hprime - ark_mem->ark_tstop)*ark_mem->ark_h > ZERO ) {
1685  ark_mem->ark_hprime = (ark_mem->ark_tstop - ark_mem->ark_tn)*(ONE-FOUR*ark_mem->ark_uround);
1686  ark_mem->ark_eta = ark_mem->ark_hprime/ark_mem->ark_h;
1687  }
1688  }
1689 
1690  /* In ONE_STEP mode, copy y and exit loop */
1691  if (itask == ARK_ONE_STEP) {
1692  istate = ARK_SUCCESS;
1693  ark_mem->ark_tretlast = *tret = ark_mem->ark_tn;
1694  N_VScale(ONE, ark_mem->ark_ycur, yout);
1695  ark_mem->ark_next_h = ark_mem->ark_hprime;
1696  break;
1697  }
1698 
1699  } /* end looping for internal steps */
1700 
1701  return(istate);
1702 }

810  if (ark_mem->ark_ynew != NULL) {
811  if (resize == NULL) {
812  N_VDestroy(ark_mem->ark_ynew);
813  ark_mem->ark_ynew = N_VClone(y0);
814  } else {
815  if (resize(ark_mem->ark_ynew, y0, resize_data)) {
816  arkProcessError(ark_mem, ARK_ILL_INPUT, "ARKODE",
817  "ARKodeResize", MSGARK_RESIZE_FAIL);
818  return(ARK_ILL_INPUT);
819  }
820  }
821  ark_mem->ark_lrw += lrw_diff;
822  ark_mem->ark_liw += liw_diff;
823  }
824 
825 
826  /* Resize fixed-point solver memory */
827  if (ark_mem->ark_use_fp) {
828  ier = arkResizeFPData(ark_mem, resize, resize_data,
829  lrw_diff, liw_diff);
830  if (ier != ARK_SUCCESS) {
831  arkProcessError(ark_mem, ARK_MEM_FAIL, "ARKODE",
832  "ARKodeResize", MSGARK_MEM_FAIL);
833  return(ARK_MEM_FAIL);
834  }
835  }
836 
837 
838  /* Copy y0 into ark_ycur to set the current solution */
839  N_VScale(ONE, y0, ark_mem->ark_ycur);
840 
841  /* Load updated error weights */
842  ier = ark_mem->ark_efun(ark_mem->ark_ycur,
843  ark_mem->ark_ewt,
844  ark_mem->ark_e_data);
845  if (ier != 0) {
846  if (ark_mem->ark_itol == ARK_WF)
847  arkProcessError(ark_mem, ARK_ILL_INPUT, "ARKODE",
848  "ARKodeResize", MSGARK_EWT_FAIL);
849  else
850  arkProcessError(ark_mem, ARK_ILL_INPUT, "ARKODE",
851  "ARKodeResize", MSGARK_BAD_EWT);
852  return(ARK_ILL_INPUT);
853  }
854 
855  /* Load updated residual weights */
856  if (!ark_mem->ark_rwt_is_ewt) {
857  ier = ark_mem->ark_rfun(ark_mem->ark_ycur,
858  ark_mem->ark_rwt,
859  ark_mem->ark_r_data);
860  if (ier != 0) {
861  if (ark_mem->ark_itol == ARK_WF)
862  arkProcessError(ark_mem, ARK_ILL_INPUT, "ARKODE",
863  "ARKodeResize", MSGARK_RWT_FAIL);
864  else
865  arkProcessError(ark_mem, ARK_ILL_INPUT, "ARKODE",
866  "ARKodeResize", MSGARK_BAD_RWT);
867  return(ARK_ILL_INPUT);
868  }
869  }
870 
871  /* Indicate that problem size is new */
872  ark_mem->ark_resized = TRUE;
873  ark_mem->ark_firststage = TRUE;
874 
875  /* Problem has been successfully re-sized */
876  return(ARK_SUCCESS);
877 }
